1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,730
A little over two years ago, a young man asked me to help him find a job with more future.

2
00:00:06,079 --> 00:00:12,769
He was employed as a clerk in the credit department of a mail order company and felt that he was getting nowhere.

3
00:00:13,039 --> 00:00:16,529
We talked about his past record and what he wanted to do.

4
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:25,649
After knowing something about him, I said, I admire you very much for wanting to move up the ladder to a better job and more responsibility.

5
00:00:25,839 --> 00:00:31,329
But getting a start in the kind of job you want requires a college degree these days.

6
00:00:31,599 --> 00:00:34,290
I notice you've finished three semesters.

7
00:00:34,560 --> 00:00:37,089
May I suggest you finish college?

8
00:00:37,279 --> 00:00:40,050
Going summers, you can do it in two years.

9
00:00:40,240 --> 00:00:46,930
Then I'm sure you can land the job you want, with the company you want to work for." I realize,

10
00:00:46,959 --> 00:00:52,769
he answered, that a college education would help, but it's impossible for me to go back to school.

11
00:00:53,039 --> 00:00:54,050
Impossible?

12
00:00:54,159 --> 00:00:54,690
Why?

13
00:00:54,800 --> 00:00:55,570
I asked.

14
00:00:56,079 --> 00:00:59,490
Well, for one thing, he began, I'm twenty-four.

15
00:00:59,680 --> 00:01:04,690
On top of that, my wife and I are expecting our second child in a couple of months.

16
00:01:04,959 --> 00:01:07,730
We barely get by now on what I make.

17
00:01:07,919 --> 00:01:11,490
I wouldn't have time to study since I'd have to keep my job.

18
00:01:11,599 --> 00:01:13,889
It's just impossible, that's all.

19
00:01:14,399 --> 00:01:19,730
This young man really had himself convinced that finishing college was impossible.

20
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:25,889
Then I said to him, if you believe it is impossible to finish school, then it is.

21
00:01:26,079 --> 00:01:31,889
But by the same token, if you'll just believe it is possible to return to the university,

22
00:01:32,079 --> 00:01:33,649
a solution will come.

23
00:01:33,919 --> 00:01:36,130
Now here's what I would like you to do.

24
00:01:36,320 --> 00:01:39,810
Make up your mind you are going to go back to school.

25
00:01:40,079 --> 00:01:42,930
Let that one thought dominate your thinking.

26
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:48,529
Then think, really think about how you can do it and still support your family.

27
00:01:48,880 --> 00:01:56,690
Come back in a couple of weeks and let me know what ideas you've come up with." My young friend returned two weeks later.

28
00:01:57,279 --> 00:02:00,050
I thought a lot about what you said, he began.

29
00:02:00,240 --> 00:02:03,010
I've decided I must go back to school.

30
00:02:03,279 --> 00:02:07,249
I haven't figured out all the angles yet, but I'll find a solution.

31
00:02:07,600 --> 00:02:08,930
And he did.

32
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:17,089
He managed to get a scholarship provided by a trade association, which paid his tuition, books, and incidentals.

33
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:21,010
He rearranged his work schedule so he could attend classes.

34
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:26,690
His enthusiasm and the promise of a better life won him his wife's full support.

35
00:02:27,040 --> 00:02:32,609
Together they creatively found ways to budget money and time more effectively.

36
00:02:32,960 --> 00:02:40,849
Last month, he received his degree one day and went to work the next as a management trainee for a large corporation.

37
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:43,969
Where there's a will, there is a way.

38
00:02:46,320 --> 00:02:48,209
Believe it can be done.

